The Button component provides a customizable button element that can be used for various purposes in your UI.
The Card component represents a card-like container that can be used to display various types of content.
The Input component allows users to input text or data and is commonly used in forms and user interactions.
To start the development process, make sure you have Node.js and npm installed. You can clone the repository and run 'npm install' to install dependencies.
To preview the UI components, use the 'npm start' command. This will launch a development server and open the app in your default browser.
When ready for production, use 'npm run build' to create optimized and minified production-ready assets in the 'build' folder.
We provide support through our online community forum, email, and dedicated customer support during business hours.
We aim to respond to support queries within 24 hours on business days. Complex issues might take longer to resolve.
